Package: corehydror
Title: Bayesian Flood-Frequency and Extreme-Value Analysis
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Cam", "Bracken", email = "cameron.bracken@pm.me", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: R bindings to a shared C++ port of the USACE-RMC Numerics and
    RMC.BestFit libraries for flood-frequency and extreme-value analysis.
    Provides probability distributions with density, distribution and quantile
    functions, moments, and parameter estimation (product moments, L-moments,
    maximum likelihood); Markov chain Monte Carlo sampling; and Bayesian,
    Bulletin 17C, and distribution-fitting analyses with uncertainty. Results
    are validated value-by-value against Numerics 2.1.4 and RMC.BestFit 2.0.0.
